30004046@@@@@@The figure stands at 52% for paper/cardboard waste, possibly due to the efforts of Karang Guni men to whom people sell their used newspapers to for a token incentive sum.@@@@1@30@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:928@LMC@2019-06-14
30004047@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:929@LMC@2019-06-14
30004048@@@@@@Despite numerous government-recycling campaigns, an Asiaone article recently reported that domestic recycling rates have actually dipped to 19% in 2014, down from 22% in 2010 [2].@@@@1@26@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:930@LMC@2019-06-14
30004049@@@@@@This is despite the Housing Development Board’s initiative to place common recycling bins in-between every 5 blocks.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:931@LMC@2019-06-14
30004050@@@@@@However, people may not be willing to go out of their ways to recycle a stack of soda bottles, when they can just throw them away from their in-unit refuse chutes.@@@@1@31@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:932@LMC@2019-06-14
30004051@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:933@LMC@2019-06-14
30004052@@@@@@Research conducted by Greenredeem UK has shown that people want to get rewarded for their recycling efforts [3].@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:934@LMC@2019-06-14
30004053@@@@@@As an incentive to get more people to recycle, I propose the SmartBin – a recycling bin that rewards people for their recycling efforts.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:935@LMC@2019-06-14
30004054@@@@@@When people put their recyclables into the SmartBin, the system would generate a token, which people could use to redeem goodies from sponsors.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:936@LMC@2019-06-14
30004055@@@@@@The more recyclables a person submits, the more attractive the incentive.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:937@LMC@2019-06-14
30004056@@@@@@Benefits@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:143; ntucle-sid:938@LMC@2019-06-14
