30004078@@@@@@Mapping NTU@@@@1@2@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:967@LMC@2019-06-14
30004079@@@@@@Date of Submission:@@@@1@3@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:971@LMC@2019-06-14
30004080@@@@@@BACKGROUND@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:972@LMC@2019-06-14
30004081@@@@@@Navigation in and out of buildings is amongst the primary concerns of students at NTU.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:973@LMC@2019-06-14
30004082@@@@@@There have been several instances where students entered the wrong building despite directions being provided, and reached late for their classes.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:974@LMC@2019-06-14
30004083@@@@@@NTU’s recent jump [1] in status calls for a better set of facilities and services for its students.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:975@LMC@2019-06-14
30004084@@@@@@PROBLEM@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:976@LMC@2019-06-14
30004085@@@@@@NTU Campus Map has some prominent flaws; its 2-dimensional floor layout is highly incomprehensible and is based on an outdated technology.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:977@LMC@2019-06-14
30004086@@@@@@Features such as Street View do not function inside buildings [2].@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:978@LMC@2019-06-14
30004087@@@@@@Moreover, NTU Campus Map is not available for every operating system (OS).@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:979@LMC@2019-06-14
30004088@@@@@@Hence, students are often late because they lose their way to classes.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:980@LMC@2019-06-14
30004089@@@@@@An interactive mobile application packed with updated technology will therefore ensure that students get to their classes quickly with a few touches.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:981@LMC@2019-06-14
30004090@@@@@@SOLUTION@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:982@LMC@2019-06-14
30004091@@@@@@The proposal is to develop a smart mobile app that will cater to the needs of students on campus.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:983@LMC@2019-06-14
30004092@@@@@@The application will require students to login using iNTU login details.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:984@LMC@2019-06-14
30004093@@@@@@This will help the application to retrieve and store useful information about the students such as their STARS PLANNER and the location of their classes.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:985@LMC@2019-06-14
30004094@@@@@@Hence, the users would not need to type in their classroom destinations.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:986@LMC@2019-06-14
30004095@@@@@@Mapping NTU will also include an advanced version of NTU Campus Map which will display 360° Panoramic View of buildings, streets and floor layouts around campus.@@@@1@26@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:987@LMC@2019-06-14
30004096@@@@@@Lastly, the App will feature voice navigation and GPS tracking to ease students’ journey to classes in a shorter time.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:988@LMC@2019-06-14
30004097@@@@@@BENEFITS@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:989@LMC@2019-06-14
30004098@@@@@@Mapping NTU will be tailored for students travelling inside campus and hence, is specifically for NTU and NIE students.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:990@LMC@2019-06-14
30004099@@@@@@The app aims at ensuring that students find their way and reach their classes in time.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:991@LMC@2019-06-14
30004100@@@@@@Mapping NTU will also be useful for freshmen and exchange students, since they are not accustomed to the places around campus.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:992@LMC@2019-06-14
30004101@@@@@@IMPLEMENTATION@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:993@LMC@2019-06-14
30004102@@@@@@A team of photographers, map developers and software developers will coordinate to build the mobile app using the following steps:@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:994@LMC@2019-06-14
30004103@@@@@@1) Overlapping panoramic photographs of streets, buildings and in-building pathways will be captured using a panoramic camera.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:995@LMC@2019-06-14
30004104@@@@@@2) These overlapping photographs will be digitally stitched together to create a 360° view.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:996@LMC@2019-06-14
30004105@@@@@@3) To construct 3D models of nearby objects, two laser sensors will send impulses and measure how quickly signals from such surfaces are reflected.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:997@LMC@2019-06-14
30004106@@@@@@4) Map developers will then use the overlapping photographs and reflection data to constitute the 360° Panoramic View.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:998@LMC@2019-06-14
30004107@@@@@@5) A software development team will add voice-navigation and GPS tracking to 360° Panoramic View and develop the mobile app for Windows, iOS, and Android Operating System.@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:144; ntucle-sid:999@LMC@2019-06-14
