30004169@@@@@@Dual-display Television – The Better Television@@@@1@6@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:957@LMC@2019-06-14
30004170@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:958@LMC@2019-06-14
30004171@@@@@@Watching television has always been a favourite pastime of many people, irrespective of genders and ages.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:959@LMC@2019-06-14
30004172@@@@@@According to a study targeting adults in 2004, Europeans watched about 3.75 hours while Americans spent almost 21% of their times watching television daily.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:960@LMC@2019-06-14
30004173@@@@@@[1] Besides that, a study conducted in Brazil verifies that 60% of children below 8 watch more than 2 hours daily, out of 616 children with almost equal number of both genders.@@@@1@32@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:961@LMC@2019-06-14
30004174@@@@@@[2] Hence, quarrel is sometimes unavoidable among family members who have contrasting preferences of programmes.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:962@LMC@2019-06-14
30004175@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:963@LMC@2019-06-14
30004176@@@@@@Each one would snatch the television remote controller away from others to watch the programme he desires, engendering deterioration of family relations.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:964@LMC@2019-06-14
30004177@@@@@@A person watching television might deliberately turn up the volume of the speakers, affecting others who want to focus on their studies or work.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:965@LMC@2019-06-14
30004178@@@@@@For two users watching different channels simultaneously on the same screen, a conventional method would be split-screen viewing, which results in smaller yet confusing display.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:966@LMC@2019-06-14
30004179@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:967@LMC@2019-06-14
30004180@@@@@@The dual-display technology blends two display inputs into one single output.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:968@LMC@2019-06-14
30004181@@@@@@The screen has alternating rows (or columns) of pixels emitting polarised light in perpendicular directions, displaying the output of corresponding images.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:969@LMC@2019-06-14
30004182@@@@@@Users wearing polarisers only see one particular image.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:970@LMC@2019-06-14
30004183@@@@@@Therefore, two people can utilise the television at the same instant.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:971@LMC@2019-06-14
30004184@@@@@@To address the problem of different sounds produced, television viewers will have to wear wireless headphones accordingly.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:972@LMC@2019-06-14
30004185@@@@@@Benefits@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:973@LMC@2019-06-14
30004186@@@@@@Not only users can watch two programmes simultaneously, innovation further leads to better gaming experience.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:974@LMC@2019-06-14
30004187@@@@@@Gamers no longer would view another player’s screen and cheat unintentionally.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:975@LMC@2019-06-14
30004188@@@@@@Putting on the headphones, users can now listen to their programmes loudly without creating noises to their companions.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:976@LMC@2019-06-14
30004189@@@@@@Also, viewers can leave shortly for a snack or for toilet and still do not lose track.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:977@LMC@2019-06-14
30004190@@@@@@Implementation@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:978@LMC@2019-06-14
30004191@@@@@@To put this proposal into work, the following steps are to be implemented:@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:979@LMC@2019-06-14
30004192@@@@@@1@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:980@LMC@2019-06-14
30004193@@@@@@We will collaborate with a television screen manufacturer to create a prototype which integrates alternating pixels emitting differently-polarised light.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:146; ntucle-sid:981@LMC@2019-06-14
