30004251@@@@@@Implementation of automated ramp on SBS buses@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1008@LMC@2019-06-14
30004252@@@@@@Implementation of automated ramp on SBS buses@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1012@LMC@2019-06-14
30004253@@@@@@Background:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1013@LMC@2019-06-14
30004254@@@@@@Although Singapore continue to experience economic growth and the welfare of the people has increased, ageing population remains a challenge to be solve.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1014@LMC@2019-06-14
30004255@@@@@@There will be a smaller ratio of working adults to each elderly above 65, from 13.5 in 1970 to 5.5 in 2013.i Some elderly will find it hard to access to the outside world as they need to sit on wheelchair due to sickness or accidents.@@@@1@46@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1015@LMC@2019-06-14
30004256@@@@@@Problem:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1016@LMC@2019-06-14
30004257@@@@@@Singapore Bus Services (SBS) offered wheelchair-accessible bus so that passenger in wheelchair will have a greater accessibility.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1017@LMC@2019-06-14
30004258@@@@@@Currently, 90% of SBS bus services are wheelchair-friendly.ii However, the ramp on these buses need to be operated manually by the bus captain.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1018@LMC@2019-06-14
30004259@@@@@@Whenever there is a passenger in wheelchair who want to board the bus, the bus captain will have to open the rear door, put down the ramp physically and then push the person inside (Fig.1).@@@@1@35@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1019@LMC@2019-06-14
30004260@@@@@@The front door will not be open in the meantime and the people outside will have to wait for a longer time (5-10minutes).@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1020@LMC@2019-06-14
30004261@@@@@@The time waiting may cause inconvenience to the other passengers especially during peak hours (7-9am) and (5-7pm).@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1021@LMC@2019-06-14
30004262@@@@@@Solution:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1022@LMC@2019-06-14
30004263@@@@@@The ramp can be modified to become automated instead.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1023@LMC@2019-06-14
30004264@@@@@@The bus captain can press a button for the ramp to be remotely put down for the passenger in wheelchair to come up the bus (Fig.2).@@@@1@26@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1024@LMC@2019-06-14
30004265@@@@@@The button can be placed near the steering wheel for the bus captain to press the button when needed.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1025@LMC@2019-06-14
30004266@@@@@@Since the surface of the wheelchair is approximately 760mm x 760mmiii, the size of the ramp can be 850mm x 850mm so as to have additional space for larger wheelchair.@@@@1@30@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1026@LMC@2019-06-14
30004267@@@@@@After the button is pressed, the ramp will extend outward to the platform so that the wheelchair-bound person can go up the ramp.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1027@LMC@2019-06-14
30004268@@@@@@Meanwhile, the other people can also start boarding the bus from the front door.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1028@LMC@2019-06-14
30004269@@@@@@This will save the waiting time for the bus captain to manually assist the passenger in wheelchair.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1029@LMC@2019-06-14
30004270@@@@@@Benefits:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1030@LMC@2019-06-14
30004271@@@@@@Firstly, the bus captain will not have to move about and physically do all the work as he just need to press a button for the ramp to automatically extend to the platform.@@@@1@33@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1031@LMC@2019-06-14
30004272@@@@@@Next, the wheelchair-bound person will still be able to board the bus with ease.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1032@LMC@2019-06-14
30004273@@@@@@Lastly, the other passengers do not need to wait for the bus captain to finish helping the wheelchair-bound person before they can board the bus.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1033@LMC@2019-06-14
30004274@@@@@@This will be a more efficient method and reduces the travelling time.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1034@LMC@2019-06-14
30004275@@@@@@Implementation:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1035@LMC@2019-06-14
30004276@@@@@@SBS can coordinate with some electronics companyiv so as to change the existing ramp to automated ramp.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1036@LMC@2019-06-14
30004277@@@@@@The time for the ramp to extend outward should be less than 10seconds so that the wheelchair-bound person can board the bus faster.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1037@LMC@2019-06-14
30004278@@@@@@Costs:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1038@LMC@2019-06-14
30004279@@@@@@The price to install one automated ramp will be $400 per bus, including the button near the steering wheel.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1039@LMC@2019-06-14
30004280@@@@@@Conclusion:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1040@LMC@2019-06-14
30004281@@@@@@Although most SBS buses are wheelchair friendly, it is not as efficient as the ramp has to be put down manually by the bus captain and other passengers have to wait for a longer time to board the bus.@@@@1@39@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1041@LMC@2019-06-14
30004282@@@@@@After the implementation of the automated ramp, these problems can be solved and everyone can have a better ride.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:149; ntucle-sid:1042@LMC@2019-06-14
